OL,3,CAlcohol deaths fall in Dumfries and
OL,4,CGalloway but rise in Scottish Borders
OL,6,FIn 2023 in Dumfries and Galloway, 32
OL,7,Fpeople died as a result of alcohol
OL,8,Frelated causes, down from 36 in 2022.
OL,10,FAlthough that number has fallen from
OL,11,F2022, it is still the second highest
OL,12,Fnumber of alcohol deaths recorded in
OL,13,FDumfries and Galloway.
OL,15,FIn the Scottish Borders the number of
OL,16,Falcohol related deaths increased by
OL,17,Fone from 21 to 22.
OL,19,FThis is the highest number of recorded
OL,20,Fdeaths in the region since 2007, when
OL,21,Fthere were also 22.
