OL,3,CAlcohol deaths fall in Dumfries and
OL,4,CGalloway but rise in Scottish Borders
OL,6,FThe figures in the south of Scotland
OL,7,Fhave risen dramatically since 1979,
OL,8,Fwhere in the Scottish Borders there
OL,9,Fwas one death and in Dumfries and
OL,10,FGalloway there were four deaths.
OL,12,FPhillipa Haxton, Head of Vital Events
OL,13,FStatistics, said: "The rate of alcohol-
OL,14,Fspecific deaths peaked in 2006 and
OL,15,Fthen fell until 2012. Since then it
OL,16,Fhas generally risen.
OL,18,F"Those aged 45-64 and 65-74 continue
OL,19,Fto have the highest mortality rates.
OL,20,FIf we look at the average age at
OL,21,Fdeath, that has risen over time.
