OL,3,CAlcohol deaths fall in Dumfries and
OL,4,CGalloway but rise in Scottish Borders
OL,6,F"The mortality rates for those aged 65
OL,7,Fto 74, and 75 and over, were at their
OL,8,Fhighest since we began recording these
OL,9,Ffigures in 1994.
OL,11,F"As the same time for age 25-44 the
OL,12,Fmortality rate has been fairly stable
OL,13,Fover the last decade."
OL,15,FThe statistics for 2023 also showcased
OL,16,Fthat the deaths caused by alcohol were
OL,17,F4.5 times as high in deprived areas
OL,18,Fcompared to the least deprived areas.
